<TITLE> General Moeen meets all sports federation presidents Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 31 (bdnews24.com) - The chairman of the National Sports Council (NSC), Army chief General Moeen U Ahmed, is to sit at a meeting with the presidents of all national sports federations Thursday. The NSC Tuesday faxed invitations to all federation presidents, mostly government appointees. "It is a courtesy meeting, where the new chairman will be introduced to the federation presidents," NSC secretary Aminul Islam Khan told bdnews24.com Tuesday. It's learnt that the NSC chairman, also president of the Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA), might discuss the prospects and problems of the different federations. "The meeting is likely to discuss problems the federations are facing and whether they can maintain the annual calendar properly," said BOA chief executive Col. (rtd) Waliullah. Waliullah said that the meeting might want to know from the federation presidents how much they were aware about the activities of their federations. After the meeting with the federation presidents, General Moeen is scheduled to meet the BOA executive committee members. 
